The paper discusses a modal logic that deals with provability and logical reflection, which are topics commonly studied in the field of logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of this logic in logic programming (cs.PL) and its potential applications in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper presents natural deduction and sequent calculus forms, which are topics commonly studied in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses proof theory, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of data structures (cs.DS).
